'''Svartidauði''' are an Icelandic [[black metal]] band from [[Kópavogur]], [[Reykjavík]]<ref name="Facebook about page">{{cite web | url = https://www.facebook.com/svartidaudi/info | title = Facebook about page | accessdate = May 2, 2014}}</ref> that formed in 2002. The name 'Svarti Dauði' is Icelandic for "Black Death".<ref name="name translation">{{cite web | url = https://translate.google.com/#is/en/Svarti%20Dau%C3%B0i | title = Google Translate Svarti Daudi | accessdate = May 2, 2014}}</ref> They released three demos before they released their debut album ''Flesh Cathedral'' on Terratur Possessions in 2012, as well as a split EP with the [[Chile]]an black metal band 'Perdition'. ''Flesh Cathedral'' was received well by the metal press, gaining positive reviews from websites such as Metal-Fi,<ref name="Flesh Cathedral Metal-Fi review">{{cite web | url = http://www.metal-fi.com/svartidaudi-flesh-cathedral/ | title = Svartidaudi – Flesh Cathedral Metal-Fi review | date = November 5, 2012 | accessdate = May 2, 2014}}</ref> Lurker's Path,<ref name="Flesh Cathedral Lurker's Path review">{{cite web | url = http://www.lurkerspath.com/2012/07/01/svartidaudi-flesh-cathedral/ | title = Svartidauði – Flesh Cathedral Lurker's Path review | date = July 1, 2012 | accessdate = May 2, 2014}}</ref> Metal Ireland,<ref name="Metal Ireland Flesh Cathedral review">{{cite web | url = http://www.metalireland.com/2012/09/12/svartidaudi-flesh-cathedral/ | title = Metal Ireland Flesh Cathedral review | date = 11 July 2012 | accessdate = May 2, 2014}}</ref> and LA Music Blog.<ref name="Flesh Cathedral LA Music Blog review">{{cite web | url = http://lamusicblog.com/2012/12/review/svartidaudi-flesh-cathedral/ | title = LA Music Blog Album Review: Svartidauði – Flesh Cathedral | date = December 7, 2012 | accessdate = May 2, 2014}}</ref> Iceland Music Export writes that the band is "Already infamous for their chaotic and often violent live shows in their native Iceland..."<ref name="Iceland Music Export Band page">{{cite web | url = http://www.icelandmusic.is/music/artists/svartidaudi/685 | title = Iceland Music Export Svartidaudi | date = | accessdate = May 2, 2014}}</ref>

==History==
On March 3, 2014, Svartidauði announced the release of a new EP titled ''The Synthesis of Whore and Beast'', due out on 30 April 2014 through Terratur Possessions and Daemon Worship Productions.<ref name="Synthesis of Whore and Beast announcement Metal Storm">{{cite web | url = http://www.metalstorm.net/events/news_comments.php?news_id=22871 | title = Svartidauði - Streaming New Song  | date = March 3, 2014 | accessdate = May 2, 2014}}</ref><ref name="Daemon Worship Productions news">{{cite web | url = http://daemonworship.org/index.php | title = Daemon Worship Production news | date = March 2, 2014 | accessdate = May 2, 2014}}</ref> The EP was produced by Stephen Lockhart at Studio Emissary and will be available on CD and 12" vinyl.<ref name="Synthesis of Whore and Beast Facebook announcement post">{{cite web | url = https://www.facebook.com/svartidaudi/photos/pb.231304270235006.-2207520000.1399066725./704882079543887/?type=3&theater | title = Synthesis of Whore and Beast Facebook announcement post | date = March 3, 2014 | accessdate = May 2, 2014}}</ref> Reviewing the EP, Lords of Metal gave it 95/100 and wrote that "you are left broken, your twisted finger going for the play button and full of joy you dive back into the hell only Svartidauði can deliver."<ref name="Lords of Metal Synthesis review">{{cite web | url = http://www.lordsofmetal.nl/en/reviews/view/id/26747 | title = Lords of Metal Svartidaudi - The Synthesis Of Whore And Beast | date = April 1, 2014 | accessdate = May 2, 2014}}</ref>

On March 5, 2014, the band played at the Kings of Black Metal Festival 2014 alongside famous black metal bands such as [[Mayhem (band)|Mayhem]], [[Hate (band)|Hate]], and [[Behexen]].<ref name="Kings of Black Metal Festival 2014">{{cite web | url = https://www.facebook.com/svartidaudi/photos/a.405042972861134.97645.231304270235006/683979524967476/?type=1&theater | title = Kings of Black Metal Festival 2014 | date = March 21, 2014| accessdate = May 2, 2014}}</ref>

On March 7, 2014, Svartidauði headlined on a European tour called 'Untamed and Unchained 2014' with Mgła, A Thousand Lost Civilizations, and One Tail, One Head.<ref name="Untamed and Unchained tour">{{Cite web | url = https://www.facebook.com/svartidaudi/photos/pb.231304270235006.-2207520000.1399066186./661969820501780/?type=3&theater | title = Untamed and Unchained tour | date = | accessdate = May 2, 2014}}</ref> which covered [[Poland]], [[Italy]], [[Switzerland]], [[The United Kingdom]], [[Belgium]] and more. The band also took part in the Speyer Grey Mass festival in [[Germany]] on March 15, 2014, alongside such bands as [[Ofermod]], [[Archgoat]], Pseudogod, and Funeral Winds.<ref name="Speyer Grey Mass festival 2014">{{cite web | url = https://www.facebook.com/svartidaudi/photos/pb.231304270235006.-2207520000.1399066186./667290529969709/?type=3&theater | title = Speyer Grey Mass 2014 lineup dates | accessdate = May 2, 2014}}</ref><ref name="Speyer Grey Mass festival 2014 last.fm event page">{{cite web | url = http://www.last.fm/festival/3732115+Speyer+Grey+Mass | title = Speyer Grey Mass at Halle 101 (Speyer) on 14 Mar 2014 | accessdate = May 2, 2014}}</ref>

On March 23, 2014, the band confirmed that they would be performing at Aurora Infernalis in the [[Netherlands]] on October 25, 2014, alongside Sapientia and Mortuus from Sweden, and Cult of Fire from [[Czech Republic]].<ref name="Aurora Infernalis Svartidaudi facebook post">{{cite web | url = https://www.facebook.com/svartidaudi/photos/pb.231304270235006.-2207520000.1399066725./715067391858689/?type=3&theater | title = Aurora Infernalis Svartidaudi Facebook post | date = March 23, 2014 | accessdate = May 2, 2014}}</ref><ref name="Aurora Infernalis IV last.fm event page">{{cite web | url = http://www.last.fm/festival/3837750+Aurora+Infernalis+Festival+Part+VI:+Cosmic+Spheres+Of+Death | title = Aurora Infernalis Festival Part VI: Cosmic Spheres Of Death on Saturday 25 October 2014  - Last.fm | date = | accessdate = May 2, 2014}}</ref>

On September 6, 2017 it was announced that guitarist Nökkvi Gylfgason had departed from the band.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/svartidaudi/posts/1602522789779807|title=Svartidauði|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=2017-10-07}}</ref> On September 7, the band announced that they would be releasing a new 7" EP during their 2017 'Continental Crucifixion' tour with [[Bölzer]], [[Archgoat]], and Eggs of Gomorrh.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/svartidaudi/photos/a.405042972861134.97645.231304270235006/1602532949778791/?type=3|title=Svartidauði|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=2017-10-07}}</ref> On September 15, the band announced that they had entered the studio to begin the recording process for a second full-length album titled ''Revelations of the Red Sword'' which was released through Ván Records on December 3, 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/svartidaudi/posts/1611077345591018|title=Svartidauði|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=2017-10-07}}</ref>

==Discography==

===Albums===
* ''Flesh Cathedral'' (2012, Terratur Possessions)<ref name="Terratur Possessions releases">{{cite web | url = http://www.terraturpossessions.com/index2.html | title = Terratur Possessions | accessdate = May 2, 2014}}</ref>
* ''Revelations of the Red Sword'' (2018, [[Ván Records]])

===EPs===
* ''Perdition / Svartidauði Split'' (2012, World Terror Committee)<ref name="World Terror Committee news article">{{cite web | url = http://w-t-c.org/__site/pages/posts/perdition-svartidaudi--split-ep--out-now141.php | title = Perdition / Svartidauði - Split EP - OUT NOW! | date = 13 January 2012 | accessdate = May 2, 2014}}</ref>
* ''The Synthesis of Whore and Beast'' (2014, Terratur Possessions/Daemon Worship Productions)<ref name="Daemon Worship Productions news" />
* ''Hideous Silhouettes of Lynched Gods'' (2016, Terrarur Possessions)<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://noisey.vice.com/en_uk/article/64yebn/svartidaudi-new-ep-2016|title=Icelandic Black Metal Gods Svartidauði Unveil 'Hideous Silhouettes of Lynched Gods'|date=2016-04-21|work=Noisey|access-date=2017-10-07|language=en-uk}}</ref>
* ''Untitled'' (2017, Ván Records)

===Demos===
* ''The Temple of Deformation'' (2006, self-released, re-issued on CD 2010)
* ''Adorned With Fire'' (2009, self-released)
* ''Those Who Crawl and Slither Shall Again Inherit the Earth'' (2010, self-released)

==Band members==

===Current members===
* Magnús - [[Drum kit|Drums]]
* Þórir - [[Guitars]]
* Sturla Viðar - [[Bass guitar|Bass]], [[vocals]]

===Live members===
* Gústaf "G.E." Evensen - Guitars (2017–present)

===Former members===
* Gunnar - [[Bass guitar|Bass]]
* Egill Þór - [[Bass guitar|Bass]]
* Birkir - [[Bass guitar|Bass]]
* Hafþór - [[Drum kit|Drums]]
* Næturfrost - [[Guitars]]
* Nökkvi - [[Guitars]] (?-2017)

